CHECK:LINE_SPACING: Please don't use multiple blank lines
#191: FILE: drivers/spi/spi_bitbang.c:519:
+
+

Vertical space is wasted given the limited number of lines an
editor window can display when multiple blank lines are used.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*spi_gpio)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct spi_gpio)...)
#202: FILE: drivers/spi/spi_gpio.c:281:
+	spi_gpio = kzalloc(sizeof(struct spi_gpio), GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*p)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct sh_msiof_spi_priv)...)
#268: FILE: drivers/spi/spi_sh_msiof.c:545:
+	p = kzalloc(sizeof(struct sh_msiof_spi_priv), GFP_KERNEL);

WARNING:OOM_MESSAGE: Possible unnecessary 'out of memory' message
#270: FILE: drivers/spi/spi_sh_msiof.c:547:
+	if (!p) {
+		dev_err(&pdev->dev, "failed to allocate private spi data\n");

CHECK:AVOID_EXTERNS: extern prototypes should be avoided in .h files
#322: FILE: include/linux/spi/spi.h:323:
+extern void spi_init_master(struct spi_master *master, struct device *dev);

Function prototypes don't need to be declared extern in .h
files.  It's assumed by the compiler and is unnecessary.

